# AI Car Concierge — Cursor Rules

## Role
Expert AI Product Engineer building a production-ready MVP on a 24-hour timeline.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11+)
- Frontend: Streamlit
- Database: SQLite (`inventory.sql` → `car_inventory.db`)
- RAG: Lightweight in-memory or Chroma + OpenAI embeddings
- LLM: OpenAI (`gpt-4o-mini` extraction, `gpt-4o` responses when needed)
- Email: Resend API

## Architectural Rules
1. SPEED & SIMPLICITY: Flat Python modules. No LangGraph, AutoGen, or hexagonal/DDD layers.
2. DETERMINISTIC OVER LLM: Structured outputs (Pydantic) for extraction only. Safe parameterized SQL in Python — never free-form Text-to-SQL.
3. HIERARCHY OF TRUTH: `policy.md` (2022+ sales only) overrides DB. Pre-2022 vehicles are "Pending De-listing"; block purchase and reservation.
4. AUTOMATION VALIDATION: Email and DB writes only after validated structured parameters.

## Coding
- FastAPI + Pydantic v2
- Graceful JSON errors, no raw tracebacks to clients
- Concise, scannable implementations
